ESP32-Based custom handheld gaming device integrating a SPI TFT display, input controls, and battery-powered hardware into a compact form factor. Designed circuit layout to incorporate analog and digital inputs while mitigating interference. Implemented firmware for SPI peripherals and GPIO-driven buttons/joystick, including debouncing, state machine menu navigation, and basic game loops under tight timing and memory constraints. Developed the power subsystem with Li-ion battery, charging, and regulation, and validated the design through iterative prototyping, oscilloscope-based signal debugging, and performance testing. Documented hardware schematics, PCB layout decisions, and firmware architecture.

This folder includes the operating system code, circuit diagrams and images.
